[b][size=14pt]Installation Guide: Debugger GDB/MI Plugin[/size][/b]
A CodeBlocks plugin using the machine interface of the GDB debugger.

[i]For Code::Blocks Nightly Build 260409_rev13831_win64 only.[/i]

[color=blue][url=https://github.com/pecanh/debugger_gdbmi]Download github binary zip[/url][/color]
Source is available at github [color=blue][url=https://github.com/pecanh/debugger_gdbmi]Source[/url][/color]
[hr]
[b]1. Preparation[/b]
• Ensure Code::Blocks is [b]not running[/b].
• Extract the ZIP contents into a temporary folder.
• [b]Note:[/b] While installing, the .exe, .dll, and .zip files must stay together.

[b]2. Installation[/b]
• Run [color=blue][b]InstallDebuggerMI.exe[/b][/color].
• Select your Code::Blocks Nightly folder when prompted.
• [i]Constraint:[/i] Your CB Nightly version date must match the install zips file name date.
• Installing into a mismatched nightly version will cause it to stall and crash.

[b]3. Configuration[/b]
Inside Code::Blocks, go to:
[b]Settings -> Debugger -> GDB/MI default[/b]
• Executable Path: Browse to your [b]gdb.exe[/b].
• Verify the othe options meet your requirements.
• Click on Ok button.

[b]4. Usage[/b]
Go to [b]Debug -> Active Debuggers[/b] and select [b]GDB/MI default[/b].

[hr]
[size=8pt]Report issues in this thread with your Nightly Build date and OS.[/size]
